    <main>
        <section class="section__container zumba__container">
            <h1 class="section__header">Zumba at FIT-TRACK</h1>
            <p class="section__description">
                Experience the joy of fitness through our high-energy Zumba classes. Our expert instructors will guide you through fun, dance-based workouts that feel more like a party than exercise!
            </p>

            <div class="zumba-types">
                <h2>Types of Zumba Classes</h2>
                <p>At FIT-TRACK, we offer various Zumba classes to suit different preferences and fitness levels:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Zumba Fitness:</strong> The original Zumba class, featuring Latin and World rhythms.</li>
                    <li><strong>Zumba Toning:</strong> Incorporates light weights for added resistance training.</li>
                    <li><strong>Aqua Zumba:</strong> A pool-based class that's easy on the joints.</li>
                    <li><strong>Strong by Zumba:</strong> A high-intensity interval training workout set to Zumba music.</li>
                    <li><strong>Zumba Gold:</strong> A lower-impact version perfect for beginners or older adults.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="zumba-benefits">
                <h2>Benefits of Zumba</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Burns calories and aids in weight loss</li>
                    <li>Improves cardiovascular fitness</li>
                    <li>Enhances coordination and balance</li>
                    <li>Boosts mood and reduces stress</li>
                    <li>Increases muscle strength and tone</li>
                    <li>Provides a fun, social workout experience</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="zumba-moves">
                <h2>Basic Zumba Moves</h2>
                
                <div class="zumba-move">
                    <img src="/image/assets/ZUMBA/salsa_step.jpg" alt="Salsa Step">
                    <div class="move-description">
                        <h3>1. Salsa Step</h3>
                        <p>A basic Latin dance step. Step forward with your right foot, shift your weight back to your left foot, then step in place with your right foot. Repeat on the other side.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="zumba-move">
                    <img src="/image/assets/ZUMBA/merengue_march.jpg" alt="Merengue March">
                    <div class="move-description">
                        <h3>2. Merengue March</h3>
                        <p>March in place, lifting your knees high and swinging your arms. Add some hip movement for extra flair!</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="zumba-move">
                    <img src="/image/assets/ZUMBA/cumbia.jpg" alt="Cumbia">
                    <div class="move-description">
                        <h3>3. Cumbia</h3>
                        <p>Step forward and back with one foot while the other foot taps in place. Add arm movements, like drawing a half-circle in front of you.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="zumba-move">
                    <img src="/image/assets/ZUMBA/reggaeton_stomp.jpg" alt="Reggaeton Stomp">
                    <div class="move-description">
                        <h3>4. Reggaeton Stomp</h3>
                        <p>Bend your knees and stomp your feet alternately, adding a bounce to your movement. You can add arm pumps for more intensity.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="zumba-move">
                    <img src="/image/assets/ZUMBA/samba_bounce.jpg" alt="Samba Bounce">
                    <div class="move-description">
                        <h3>5. Samba Bounce</h3>
                        <p>Keep your feet close together and bounce by bending and straightening your knees. Add some hip movement and arm swings for the full effect.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
